Without the support of the following people BlitzDms would probably have
never been as good a program as it is today. Our thanks go to:-

 -  Simon Archer for his excellent gui generating program which was used to
    create the gui for BlitzDms, and for his help in beta testing BlitzDms.

 -  Leslie Olding and Paul Lathwell who are outstanding beta testers and, due
    to their verbose reports, we didn't need to take on many others.

 -  Johnathan Forbes for creating the efficient LZX archiver

 -  Christian Wasner for writing PackDev.

 -  Adam Chapman for allowing us to include the distribution archive of XDms2.0
    with BlitzDms and giving permission for us to support it in the program. As
    it happened, only the idea was used as all the action takes place inside
    BlitzDms itself instead of through a slow Dos script.

    Note: Due to a dispute between the authors of Xdms and DiskSqueeze, Xdms is
          no longer supplied with the BlitzDms archive. Paul Juhasz and myself
          have no interest in the argument between the two parties and have
          taken the option to support both applications in our program for the
          benefit of the end-user and to remain impartial.

 -  Dirk Vael, author of DiskSqueeze!, who apparently had this idea before
    Adam Chapman and made sure we knew about it too... :*l

 -  Janice Bailey for her help in the layout of this guide and for keeping up
    the morale between long hours at the screen... And not to mention the fact
    that she cooks a great Spaghetti Bolognaise :-)

 -  Phillip Snell and Paul Nuzzo for beta testing right near the end to ensure
    we got it working properly before releasing the program for once :-)

 -  To Mat Bettinson for our intensive IRC chat discussing the program and ways
    to improve upon it, and the quickest rapid fire list of problems I've ever
    seen.

 -  To Henrik "Puh" Nilsson (alvar@one.se) and Johan "S.Duvan" Alfredsson
    (d95duvan@dtek.chalmers.se) of Oepir Risti Translations for the Swedish
    version of this guide.

 -  To Jon Peterson for handling U.S registrations on our behalf.

 -  To Amiga Format magazine for its kind comments regarding the program and
    write up in their PD section.

 -  And mostly our thanks go out to the Amiga and the community spirit it has
    always managed to instil into its users.


